25/06/2006
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Local elections were held Sunday (25 June) in the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus (TRNC), which is recognised by Turkey only. According to the election council, some 150,000 eligible voters were expected to go to the polls to elect 28 mayors and members of municipal government bodies. In parallel to the municipal elections, voting for two parliamentary members' seats will also be held in Lefkosa and Girne, to fill in the positions left vacant after Mehmet Ali Talat was elected as TRNC president and after the death deputy Salih Miroglu. (Zaman, Phileleftheros - 25/06/06; ANA - 23/06/06) 
